property.name: text
property.value:
This demo shows how to read data stream from local files or online, process the data and export the results to web. The web page is generated using Ptolemy's HTML Export Feature (in Ptolemy, File -> Export -> Export to Web)
Please double click the JSPlotter to see the graph.
The graph shows power consumption of a Cory Hall for one day, where the power consumption from lighting can be viewed individually. Data was downloaded from the Simple Measurement and Actuation Profile (sMAP) project, http://new.openbms.org/plot/ A threshold can be edited in the model to screen for usage above the threshold
